reviewText: You gotta have this DVD set. Stars from yesteryear and stock car racing from the beginning. See the men who made stockcar what is is today!
Nascar is fun, but it's history is even more fun. Check out a time when the drivers were bigger than the sponsors on the door.

If you grew up around raceing. I mean locale raceing where ever body went out on saturday nite,an race,Bomber,s,limited lates,an late models like I did.you will love this,55 Chevy,s an Fords raceing with the windows,an windshield wipers still on the cars,Guys smoken,while they race. Its the good ole days.

As described. Very pleased with purchase.

This is an excellent supplement to the books I am reading on the history of NASCAR.  I was a teenager in the mid to late 60's, and didn't watch much of this.  Now it is fascinating to see stock car racing from the period covered by the films, particularly as they were a lot more "stock" then compared to now, and the men operating the machines drove more "by the seat of their pants"!
Old American cars!! What's not to like about it!
I enjoyed it a lot
a must have for any stock car buff
I love old cars and movies about them.
good

TOP NOTCH FILMS that will be enjoyed by all who view them. You will not be disappointed!
The early racing on the beach footage is phenomenal!
Fantastic!! A must own- cannot recommend. Enough! A great look at days gone by - an impressive bargain for sure!

Good racing footage from the early days of NASCAR and several of the more exciting races.  Stock cars never were really "stock", but the ones you see in these races are as close as you will probably ever see to ones you could have actually driven off the show room floor.  The Chevy vs the World comparisons are laughable, but hey that's how they advertised back then.

It is fairly accurate.  It shows Banjo Matthews (later the car builder) quite well.  It didn't say much about the creative work that went on, but the film was actual film of the races and the announcer was neutral.
Great documentary of the golden years of Nascar racing, with all the different drivers and teams racing at all the tracks.

If your looking to see a lot about early racing this is a good video that covers a lot of information. Worth the price.
  Wayne A. Lee

An interesting account of how American stock car racing went from humble beginnings to a major sporting event. With historic footage from early races and profiles of pioneer drivers, this boxset is a must for true stock car fans.
